            <p:rationale>The integrity and confidentiality of information must be monitored. The risk classification of information determines what measures should be taken to control data integrity and confidentiality. Given the absence of an information security policy and a standard set of actions, it is necessary to implement a risk analysis system. This analysis should demonstrate whether authentication is required, or possibly even if a stronger authentication is required for the area in question. Securing excessive information increases the threshold and is not recommended.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>It is in the context of a system implementation project that a risk analysis is carried out in order to determine access control mechanisms. There are standard facilities for authentication and strong authentication of users.</p:implications>
